B.A ; Modern Literature. Also known as Molly. A member of Conradh na Gaeilge. She took part in the performance of 'Casadh an tSúgáin playing the role of Úna in the Gaiety in 1901. She one first prize in Oireachtas 1902 for her essay on Edward Fitzgerald. She also won second prize in Oireachtas 1908 for her essay on the differences between old Irish literature and modern European literature, first place in this competition was won by Pádraic Ó Conaire.  She wrote many drama's such as 'Cáit Ní Dhuibhir (1938) 'Scéal an tí' (1952). Her dramas for children were published in 'An Claidheamh Soluis', 'An Branar', 'Misneach', and 'Ar Aghaidh'. She married Seán Mac Gearailt in 1906. She was President of the Oireachtas in 1954.

In London she  was secretary of Cumann Ríoga Áiseach, she was also a member of Cumann Béaloidis and president of Cumann Liteartha na hÉireann. She was editor of The Irish Home Reading Magazine 1894. She also wrote in the Celtic Review, Literary World and Folklore Journal.
